<div id="review_41230028" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/41230028" />
    <a title="Anna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1842348-anna"><img alt="Anna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1230597236p2/1842348.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/41230028?book_show_action=true">Dec 29, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anna" href="/user/show/1842348-anna">Anna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/823770.Anthills_of_the_Savannah">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer41230028" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3801858395815073948">One thing I like about this novel is Achebe&apos;s use of creole forms. It&apos;s probably the first novel I read with extensive use of &quot;non-standard&quot; English, and I remember finding it a little difficult at first. I also found it intriguing, though, and that interest persists. Standards in language are overrated.</span>
  <span id="freeText3801858395815073948" style="display:none">One thing I like about this novel is Achebe's use of creole forms. It's probably the first novel I read with extensive use of "non-standard" English, and I remember finding it a little difficult at first. I also found it intriguing, though, and that interest persists. Standards in language are overrated.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3801858395815073948" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


